name: Konstantin Kostenko
headline: R&D Engineer
creator: False
past_company_2: Dubna International University of Nature, Society and Man
bio:
"Scientists dream about doing great things. Engineers do them." James A. Michener.

I use this approach to turn scientific ideas into a piece of hardware. Working in research institutions and scientific production companies, I am involved in a diversity of engineering and research activities. I deal with algorithm and software development, prototype design, intersystem communication, acquisition and analysis of time-series data, sensor calibration, statistical modeling, optimization, bench, and field testing. I publish the results of my research in peer-reviewed journals and conference papers.

Engineering design and many accompanying activities have always been my passion. I am always excited about an opportunity to contribute to a technological, applied, or fundamental science project.

My goals are always to do my job efficiently, creatively, responsibly, and punctually. Effective interaction with other professionals, including scientists, engineers, vendors, students, etc. is an essential part of my approach to work.

I am open to R&D engineering opportunities at universities, scientific institutions, and laboratories.

bio:
As a passionate Software Engineer with expertise in frontend engineering, Flutter development, and cloud technologies, I thrive on crafting innovative, user-centric applications that drive business growth. My journey spans building scalable web and mobile solutions, enhancing fintech platforms, and mentoring aspiring developers through leadership roles in tech communities.

Highlights of my experience include:

- Driving user engagement through clean, maintainable code and seamless UI/UX implementation.
- Improving performance and scalability for platforms in fintech and e-commerce using cutting-edge technologies like JavaScript, TypeScript, ReactJS, and Flutter.
- Collaborating on cross-functional teams to deliver high-quality, innovative applications that meet business goals.
- Leading projects in cloud migration, Augmented Reality (AR) integration, and backend optimization, resulting in measurable efficiency gains.

I'm especially passionate about empowering fintech innovation and solving challenges at the intersection of technology and entrepreneurship. With a Master's in Computer Science and certifications in cloud development and programming fundamentals, I continuously hone my skills to stay ahead in this fast-evolving field.

Let's connect if you’re looking for a software engineer to elevate your next project or need insights into optimizing tech solutions for maximum impact.

name: Daniel Elambo Atonge
headline: Passionate Software & Cloud Engineer 👨🏽‍💻
creator: False
bio:
Teaching and writing software applications for over 4 years, I have a proven track record of designing, developing, and implementing software solutions that meet and exceed client expectations. My ability to work with modern front-end technologies like React, and Angular, allows me to build scalable, robust, and secure applications. My experience with AWS and other cloud technologies allows me to build and deploy microservices, cloud-native applications, and other serverless architectures that are scalable and cost-effective.

+ Software engineer who has tried quite a number of disciplines in the software field including;
 Front-end - React (Next), Angular (Angular Universal), Vue (Nuxt)
 Mobile - React Native, Flutter
 Back-end - Express, Nestjs, Java Springboot, fastapi
 DevOps - Docker, Kubernetes, AWS, Ansible, GitHub actions.
 Research - Wrote scientific research papers on “Digital Image Forgery” and “Minimising Energy Consumption in Computer Devices”. Implemented “A static type checker for Jolie Programming Language”.
 Design - Figma.

+ From a tender age, I have been fascinated by how software affects our daily lives. Since then, my mission has been to build and contribute to software and systems that add value to people's everyday lives especially in making system more transparent and robust.

+ Understanding I still have a long journey ahead and an infinite list of things to learn in this beautiful field of software development and engineering. I will prefer working in an environment that encourages innovation and failure in an agile setting.

+ As much as I love learning, I also enjoy teaching and demystifying concepts. I have held teaching roles on several occasions at Innopolis University

bio:
Co-founder and CTO at Introwise — helping experts move their business online.

Book a free call with me: https://introwise.com/denis

Software engineer experienced in building highly-optimized software. Previously I have worked in the distributed storage project developing high performance scalable gateway advancing my knowledge in C++14 and beyond, cloud storage technologies and architectures.

Prior I have worked at Intel in a small team developing binary translation for an experimental architecture. My experience here ranges from core compilers construction theory to early hardware simulation and prototyping.

I have obtained strong fundamental knowledge from Moscow Institute of Physics and Technology and extended it to real world software engineering at world-class MSIT-SE program at Carnegie Mellon University.

I am keen on taking complex problems with a high degree of uncertainty and turning them into complete working solutions. I am using software engineering knowledge on a daily basis and always looking to make things better and more efficient given limited resources.

bio:
Hello! Nice to see on my page. 

I'm Kirill Demchenko, specializing in empowering IT companies to excel in DevOps. 

With a career spanning back to 2016, I've honed my skills within prominent Russian organizations like Sberbank, X5 Group, and Yandex Practicum. Actively engaged in DevOps and GDG communities, I thrive on organizing meetups, conferences, and other impactful events. I'm passionate about crafting educational content and mentoring others in DevOps. 

Beyond technology, I enjoy playing hockey as a defender, and I'm an avid enthusiast of roller skates and skateboarding.

name: Joseph Alexander  Brown
headline: PhD Computer Science
creator: False
bio:
Leon Battista Alberti said that "a man can do all things if he will" when referring to the Uomo Universale.  I envision myself as a polymath, one who enjoys new ideas while not letting arbitrary lines between disciplines forced by our post-industrial world block a contribution.  Information is now the driving force for change in the world and I want to make it a change for the better.

Primarily, I work with computers, which I see as being a tool.  As most tools they have their uses and can both build and destroy.  The issue is how one learns the use of the tool in a way which both gives utility to the society and to the craftsman.  Miyamoto Musashi, perhaps histories’ greatest swordsman, said that one must not have a favorite weapon, no more than a craftsman should have a favorite tool.

I never go anywhere without: a book, a watch, a pen, and a Swiss army pocket knife (unless the TSA is going to take it).  These four objects perhaps best summarize my experience.  I am an academic and an educator, a lover of history and design, a writer and creator, and a practicalist.

name: Pavel Kolychev
headline: Scrum master | Agile coach
creator: False
school_2: Baikal National University of Economic and Law
bio:
Summary
Certified Professional Scrum Master (PSM II) and SAFe Agilist with over 8 years of experience in Agile project management, product development, and team leadership. Proven track record of delivering high-impact projects across globally distributed teams in B2B and B2C environments. Expert in Scrum, Kanban, and SAFe frameworks, with a focus on process optimization, continuous delivery, and value-driven initiatives. Seeking a remote or international Agile Project Manager role to drive innovation and team excellence.

Career highlights:

name: Victor Fernando Pérez
headline: Computer Vision Engineer
creator: False
bio:
🔧 Innovative Engineer | Performance Analyst | Robotics Enthusiast

I am a results-driven engineer specializing in system performance analysis, particularly with Nvidia's Orin platform. My expertise encompasses a wide array of technologies, including GNSS, stereo vision, and advanced camera systems, as well as kernel tuning and troubleshooting within Linux ARM environments.

With a strong background in ROS 2, Python, and C++, I have developed performance testing protocols and implemented algorithms such as Kalman filters, enhancing the efficiency of autonomous driving systems. My experience extends to CUDA programming and utilizing DriveWorks for advanced driver-assistance systems (ADAS).

In addition to my work in embedded systems, I have a solid foundation in software verification and structural coverage analysis, having contributed to the development of critical aerospace applications, including the GE9X aircraft engine.

I also possess a diverse skill set in renewable energy solutions, having designed and implemented fixed and solar tracking photovoltaic systems. My passion for automation and AI drives my exploration of innovative manufacturing techniques, leveraging camera systems for enhanced production efficiency.

Proficient in a variety of modeling and simulation software, I enjoy conceptualizing and designing mechanical systems, from turbojet engines to aerodynamic structures. I thrive on challenges that combine engineering principles with creative problem-solving.

Let's connect and explore opportunities to collaborate on cutting-edge projects that push the boundaries of technology!
